ter%20part%20in%20and%20around%20Delhi%2C%20either%20with%20Shah%20Alam%20II%20or%20his%20general%2C%20Mirza%20Najaf%20Khan.%20He%20was%20disappointed%20in%20his%20expectations%20of%20making%20a%20fortune%20and%20died%20a%20miserable%20death.%20However%2C%20his%20journal%20and%20other%20papers%20reached%20France%20where%20they%20remained%20in%20the%20National%20Library%20for%20nearly%20200%20years%2C%20until%20the%20Ecole%20Nationale%20d%E2%80%99Extreme%20Orient%20published%20it%20in%20a%20carefully%20collated%20edition%20in%201971.%20This%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3EVoyage%20en%20Inde%20du%20Comte%20de%20Modave%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20has%20recently%20been%20translated%20into%20English.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20extract%20from%20%3Cspan%3ES%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eoldier%20of%20Misfortune%3A%20The%20Memoirs%20of%20the%20Comte%20de%20Modave%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eedited%20and%20annotated%20by%20Jean%20Deloche%20and%20t%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eranslated%20by%20G.%20S.%20Cheema.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20324px)%2085vw%2C%20324px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190255%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.45-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22324%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190255%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.45-PM.png%20766w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190255%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.45-PM-194x300.png%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190255%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.45-PM-664x1024.png%20664w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695708%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EG.%20S.%20Cheema%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ESoldier%20Of%20Misfortune%3A%20The%20Memoirs%20Of%20The%20Comte%20De%20Modave%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EManohar%20(2024)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20last%20the%20promised%20day%2C%20so%20earnestly%20desired%2C%20arrived%2C%20and%20though%20I%20had%20been%20informed%20the%20day%20before%2C%20I%20did%20not%20quite%20believe%20it.%20On%2024%20April%20%5B1775%5D%2C%20at%20five%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20the%20minister%20sent%20for%20me%20ceremoniously%20through%20a%20nobleman%2C%20his%20special%20confidante%2C%20one%20Raja%20Daya%20Ram%2C%20who%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20numerous%20cortege%20and%20most%20of%20those%20who%20had%20interacted%20with%20me%20since%20my%20arrival.%20This%20noble%20lord%20found%20me%20in%20the%20briefest%20possible%20dishabille.%20I%20excused%20myself%2C%20saying%20that%20I%20thought%20that%20they%20were%20playing%20games%20when%20they%20told%20me%20the%20previous%20day%20that%20my%20audience%20had%20been%20fixed.%20However%2C%20the%20raja%20sat%20down%20calmly%20at%20the%20door%20of%20my%20tent%20to%20give%20me%20time%20to%20get%20dressed%20and%20we%20proceeded%20to%20the%20palace%2C%20at%20about%20seven%20o%E2%80%99clock.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20passed%20through%20different%20courtyards%20finally%20stopping%20at%20the%20door%20to%20the%20one%20where%20the%20King%20would%20receive%20us.%20The%20opening%20was%20closed%20by%20a%20red%20coloured%20hanging.%20We%20stood%20there%20waiting%20for%20about%20three%20uarters%20of%20an%20hour%2C%20for%20no%20better%20reason%20than%20the%20need%20for%20awaiting%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20King%2C%20at%20whose%20orders%20we%20had%20come.%20We%20saw%20them%20pass%20three%20baskets%20within%2C%20and%20then%20we%20were%20called.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECeremonial%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20we%20entered%20we%20saw%20the%20King%20seated%20in%20a%20palanquin%20without%20its%20bamboos%2C%20or%20rather%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20throne%20that%20is%20supported%20by%20eight%20men%20on%20their%20shoulders.%20His%20dress%20seemed%20quite%20magnificent%20and%20his%20turban%2C%20among%20other%20things%20was%20of%20fine%20gold%20tissue%20which%20they%20make%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20prince%20had%20a%20sword%2C%20a%20bow%20and%20a%20quiver%20filled%20with%20arrows.%20His%20seat%20was%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20courtyard%2C%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20entrance%2C%20and%20he%20sat%20motionless%2C%20like%20a%20statue.%20Two%20or%20three%20hundred%20persons%20surrounded%20the%20throne%2C%20arranged%20in%20rows%20like%20a%20horseshoe%2C%20so%20that%20the%20approach%20was%20free.%20An%20old%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echobdar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20a%20baton%20in%20his%20hand%2C%20and%20his%20back%20against%20the%20gateway%20by%20which%20we%20had%20entered%2C%20gesticulated%20with%20his%20arms%20and%20legs%20like%20a%20man%20possessed%2C%20crying%20out%20with%20all%20his%20force%2C%20words%20whose%20sense%20is%20%E2%80%98Salute%20the%20King%20of%20Kings%2C%20the%20Conqueror%20of%20the%20World%2C%20the%20Master%20of%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99%20and%20other%20extravagant%20platitudes%2C%20as%20false%20as%20they%20were%20ridiculous.%20They%20led%20us%20all%20close%20to%20the%20man%2C%20and%20they%20made%20us%20do%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaam%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20was%20not%20executed%20according%20to%20the%20rigid%20Indian%20protocol.%20Thereafter%20we%20were%20conducted%20to%20the%20left%2C%20about%20three%20steps%20from%20the%20throne%20where%20we%20again%20performed%20another%20salutation.%20I%20placed%20seven%20gold%20rupees%20on%20a%20white%20handkerchief%20and%20approached%20the%20King.%20The%20monarch%20accepted%20our%20offering%20and%20gave%20them%20to%20someone%20on%20his%20right%20to%20keep.%20It%20seemed%20to%20me%20that%20he%20counted%20them.%20Messieurs%20Dieu%20and%20Moncelet%20moved%20up%20after%20me%20and%20tendered%20their%20respects%20in%20the%20same%20manner.%20We%20were%20then%20taken%20to%20the%20doorway%20where%20we%20again%20repeated%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaams%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20returned%20to%20the%20side%20of%20the%20throne.%20The%20King%20now%20looked%20at%20us%20properly%2C%20one%20after%20the%20other%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20utter%20a%20word.%20I%20noticed%20his%20minister%2C%20Abdullah%20Khan%2C%20with%20a%20painted%20baton%20in%20his%20hand%20which%20he%20kept%20shaking%20and%20he%20seemed%20to%20be%20paying%20close%20and%20affectionate%20attention%20to%20all%20our%20movements.%20The%20King%20gave%20a%20signal%20by%20saying%20two%20or%20three%20words.%20Then%20they%20grabbed%20us%20and%20we%20were%20brought%20back%20behind%20the%20doorway%20where%20we%20had%20waited%20earlier%2C%20however%20without%20having%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaam%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Khillat%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20they%20made%20us%20wear%2C%20over%20our%20French%20clothes%2C%20the%20clothes%20of%20the%20country.%20Round%20our%20caps%20they%20wound%20a%20piece%20of%20gold%20tissue.%20We%20were%20then%20given%20a%20large%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecabaye%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20if%20you%20wish%2C%20a%20cassock%20of%20those%20beautiful%20fabrics%2C%20and%20as%20I%20showed%20some%20impatience%20at%20the%20length%20of%20this%20ceremony%2C%20they%20placed%20round%20my%20neck%20the%20pieces%20intended%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20belt%2C%20and%20that%20which%20covers%20the%20toque%20or%20turban.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20presents%20are%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekhillats%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%2C%20as%20in%20Persia.%20Mine%20was%20composed%20of%20six%20pieces%20which%20formed%20the%20complete%20outfit.%20There%20were%20also%20two%20aigrettes%20set%20with%20stones%2C%20but%20they%20were%20of%20little%20value.%20The%20other%20two%20gentlemen%20received%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekhillats%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20four%20pieces.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20we%20had%20been%20so%20magnificently%20decked%20out%20they%20again%20led%20us%20up%20to%20the%20Emperor%2C%20with%20the%20same%20ceremonies%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaams%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20on%20our%20previous%20entry.%20When%20I%20was%20close%20to%20the%20person%20of%20the%20prince%20he%20made%20a%20sign%20to%20an%20officer%20who%20brought%20me%20a%20sword%20which%20I%20accepted%2C%20repeated%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaam%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20offered%20another%20present%2C%20this%20time%20of%20Rs%202%20in%20gold%2C%20which%20he%20took%20on%20the%20previous%20occasion.%20It%20was%20then%20necessary%20to%20return%20to%20the%20door%20for%20a%20fourth%20time%20and%20re-commence%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalaams%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20old%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echobdar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20gesticulated%20and%20cried%20out%20like%20a%20veritable%20demon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20returned%20close%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPadshah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20he%20looked%20at%20me%20for%20some%20moments%20without%20saying%20a%20word.%20Then%20he%20ordered%20the%20bearers%20who%20had%20brought%20him%20to%20take%20him%20back%20to%20his%20apartments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20343px)%2085vw%2C%20343px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190313%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.37-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22343%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190313%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.37-PM.png%20760w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190313%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.37-PM-192x300.png%20192w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190313%2FScreenshot-2024-02-04-at-7.02.37-PM-655x1024.png%20655w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695709%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22536%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EG.%20S.%20Cheema%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ESoldier%20Of%20Misfortune%3A%20The%20Memoirs%20Of%20The%20Comte%20De%20Modave%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EManohar%20(2024)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20conductor%2C%20who%20filled%20the%20roll%20of%20master%20of%20ceremonies%2C%20now%20led%20us%20into%20a%20vast%20and%20magnificent%20hall%20which%20is%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20side%20of%20the%20court%2C%20and%20overlooks%20a%20parterre%20on%20the%20opposite%20side.%20This%20hall%20is%20almost%20as%20large%20as%20the%20courtyard%2C%20and%20is%20supported%20by%20many%20rows%20of%20pillars.%20It%20was%20not%20so%20long%20ago%20that%20its%20ceiling%20had%20been%20of%20solid%20silver.%20It%20had%20escaped%20the%20greed%20of%20Nadir%20Shah%2C%20and%20of%20those%20before%20and%20after%2C%20who%20had%20played%20with%20the%20Mughal%20emperors.%20They%20had%20spared%20it%20out%20of%20respect%20for%20the%20dynasty%E2%80%99s%20former%20power%2C%20and%20because%20they%20had%20stayed%20in%20the%20palace.%20But%20finally%2C%20the%20Marathas%20helped%20themselves%20to%20it%2C%20as%20a%20relic%20that%20still%20had%20some%20value.%20We%20stayed%20a%20few%20minutes%20in%20this%20beautiful%20hall%2C%20seated%20on%20Patna%20carpets%20and%20left%20it%20when%20we%20were%20informed%20that%20Abdullah%20Khan%20had%20left%20the%20King.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMeeting%20with%20Abdullah%20Khan%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minister%20hastened%20to%20meet%20us%20with%20great%20eagerness%20and%20cordiality.%20He%20is%20a%20venerable%20old%20man%2C%20by%20his%20looks%20and%20the%20whiteness%20of%20his%20beard.%20He%20is%20a%20Kashmiri%2C%20and%20could%20be%20mistaken%20for%20a%20European%20by%20the%20vivacity%20of%20his%20manners%20and%20the%20fairness%20of%20his%20skin.%20He%20embraced%20all%20three%20of%20us%20and%20we%20followed%20him%20to%20a%20separate%20pavilion%2C%20where%20he%20gives%20his%20audiences.%20We%20were%20with%20him%20for%20half%20an%20hour%2C%20then%20he%20had%20some%20fabrics%20and%20shawls%20brought%20which%20he%20presented%20to%20us%20and%20saw%20us%20off.%20He%20stated%20several%20times%20that%20he%20was%20sorry%20he%20did%20not%20have%20anyone%20to%20serve%20as%20an%20interpreter%20for%20him%2C%20but%20it%20was%20entirely%20his%20fault.%20He%20had%20insisted%20and%20managed%20to%20ensure%20that%20my%20diwan%20should%20not%20be%20admitted%20to%20the%20audience%20with%20the%20King%2C%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20annoying%20intrigues%20which%20I%20had%20spoken%20of%20earlier.%20This%20was%20the%20end%20of%20our%20presentation.%20All%20this%20ceremony%20took%20up%20nearly%20three%20hours.%20I%20returned%20to%20my%20tent%20in%20the%20accoutrements%20which%20had%20been%20bestowed%20on%20me%20at%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20audience.%20It%20will%20not%20be%20out%20of%20place%20to%20add%20that%20a%20cursed%20eunuch%20pestered%20me%20for%20some%20time%20trying%20to%20extract%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebakhsheesh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20is%2C%20a%20gratification%20from%20me.%20He%20pulled%20me%20by%20my%20arms%2C%20tapped%20me%20on%20the%20shoulder%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20obstruct%20my%20passage%20as%20I%20tried%20to%20walk%20away.%20At%20first%20I%20suffered%20his%20importunities%20and%20insolence%20with%20patience%2C%20but%20finally%20I%20lost%20my%20temper.%20I%20shouted%20insults%20and%20abuses%2C%20for%20these%20are%20learnt%20first%20of%20all%20in%20all%20foreign%20languages%2C%20and%20following%20his%20example%2C%20joining%20gestures%20to%20my%20words%2C%20I%20threatened%20him%20with%20the%20sword%20that%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPadshah%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20presented%20me.%20With%20this%20I%20was%20so%20successful%20that%20I%20heard%20no%20more%20from%20him.%20We%20returned%20to%20our%20tents%20by%20ten%20in%20the%20morning.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EG.S.%20Cheema%20is%20a%20retired%20IAS%20officer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707057035000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04190925%2FMagasins_de_la_Compagnie_des_Indes_a%25CC%2580_Pondiche%25CC%2581ry.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-extract-the-memoirs-of-a-french-soldier-who-came-to-india-in-1773%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Louis%20Laurent%20de%20Federbe%2C%20Comte%20de%20Modave%2C%20came%20to%20India%20in%20hopes%20of%20making%20a%20fortune.%20After%20his%20death%2C%20his%20journal%20and%20other%20papers%20reached%20France%20where%20they%20remained%20in%20the%20National%20Library%20for%20nearly%20200%20years%20before%20being%20published.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-extract-the-memoirs-of-a-french-soldier-who-came-to-india-in-1773%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BUsed%20Condoms%2C%20Underwear%26quot%3B%3A%20Staff%20On%20%26quot%3BDisgusting%26quot%3B%20Things%20Seen%20On%20Flights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20flight%20attendant%20has%20left%20the%20internet%20stunned%20after%20revealing%20some%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bdisgusting%26quot%3B%20things%20he%20has%20seen%20on%20flights%20in%20his%20career%20spanning%2025%20years%20with%20a%20major%20US%20Airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20anonymous%20crew%20member%20conducted%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2