rm%20reforms%20to%20drive%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Budget%20has%20increased%20the%20capital%20expenditure%20outlay%20to%2011.1%20per%20cent%20to%20Rs%2011.11%20lakh%20crore.%20The%20government%20resisted%20any%20large%20giveaways%20and%20said%20it%20would%20reduce%20its%20fiscal%20deficit%20to%205.1%20per%20cent%20of%20GDP%20in%202024-25%20from%205.8%20per%20cent%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20will%20borrow%20a%20gross%20of%20Rs%2014.13%20trillion%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20starting%20April%201%2C%20compared%20with%20Rs%2015.43%20trillion%20for%20the%20current%20fiscal%2C%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Breakup%20Of%20Where%20The%20Government%20Gets%20Its%20Money%20From%20And%20Where%20It%20Spends%20It%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20Does%20Rupee%20Come%20From%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Budget%20presented%20on%20Thursday%20stated%20that%20the%20borrowings%20and%20other%20liabilities%20constitute%20the%20highest%20income%20procured%20by%20the%20Centre%2C%2028%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20income.%20Next%20is%20Income%20Tax%20(18%20per%20cent)%20followed%20by%20GST%20(18%20per%20cent%20)%20and%20Corporation%20Tax%20(17%20per%20cent).%20Non-tax%20receipts%20like%20rent%2C%20penalties%20and%20fines%20comprised%207%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20income.%20Union%20Excise%20Duties%20(five%20per%20cent)%2C%20Customs%20(four%20per%20cent)%20and%20Non-Debt%20Capital%20Receipts%20(one%20per%20cent).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fmol2mqt_rupee-1_625x300_01_February_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20Does%20Rupee%20Go%20To%3F